attributes.logicalName: Party Relationship Type Level One Code
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Level 1 code of the Party Relationship. The level 1 code represents the next level of grouping of the relationship. Some of the level 1 type codes are pertaining to household, business control and business inter connection.

attributes.logicalName: Party Relationship Type Level One Description
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Level 1 description of the Party Relationship. The level 1 description represents the next level of grouping of the relationship. Some of the level 1 type description are household, business control and business inter connection.

attributes.logicalName: Party Relationship Type Level Two Code
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Level 2 code of the Party Relationship. The level 2 code represents the next level of grouping of the relationship. Some of the level 2 type codes are pertaining to control and inter connection.

attributes.logicalName: Party Relationship Type Level Two Description
attributes.gcd: Refers to the Level 2 description of the Party Relationship. The level 2 description represents the next level of grouping of the relationship. Some of the level 2 type description are pertaining to control and inter connection.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.

Refers to the code of the party relationship between the party and the related party. The relationship type can be an affiliate, joint venture, Related Party, Significant Invested Party, common brand name, promoters, Non Operative Financial Holding as NOFHC, parent, spouse etc. For example, in FDIC relationship type can be OC as Official Custodian, BEN as Beneficiary, BHR as Bond Holder, MOR as Mortgagor.

Refers to the code of the party relationship between the party and the related party. The relationship type can be an affiliate, joint venture, Related Party, Significant Invested Party, common brand name, promoters, Non Operative Financial Holding as NOFHC, parent, spouse etc. For example, in FDIC relationship type can be OC as Official Custodian, BEN as Beneficiary, BHR as Bond Holder, MOR as Mortgagor.

Refers to the description of the Party Relationship. The relationship type can be an affiliate, joint venture, Related Party, a direct or indirect ownership of 20 percent or more interest in the voting power of the enterprise, common brand name, promoters, Non Operative Financial Holding Company as NOFHC, parent, spouse etc.
Refers to the equivalent numeric identifier of the Relationship Type.
